      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not defined — factor deemed outside COU scope by assessment team.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that use error pertains to clinical operator interaction with the physical CPB device, not to the simulation workflow. As a result, this factor was not evaluated as part of the credibility assessment. The team's position is that simulation software operation by trained engineers does not constitute 'use' in the medical device sense, and therefore this factor does not apply to the COU. No formal not-applicable designation was recorded in the evidence package, and no alternative controls for simulation operator error (e.g., independent peer review of boundary condition setup, checklist-based input verification) were documented or assessed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified for rotating internal flow; hemolysis constitutive model validated against published data; model form uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for rotating pump geometries (Hariharan et al. 2011). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model calibrated against three independent datasets. Sensitivity of RH to turbulence model choice quantified: ±8% variation across SST, realizable k-epsilon, and RSM. Model form uncertainty explicitly bounded. Required level met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties sourced from traceable measurements or published literature; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles derived from Coriolis meter measurements (±0.5%). Blood viscosity modeled using Carreau-Yasuda fit to rheometry data (R²=0.997). Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of physical pump (±0.01 mm). One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for all primary inputs; hematocrit and viscosity identified as dominant uncertainty sources, contributing ±6% to RH. Required level met."
    },
